# phisher-man

**The Phisherman** is a simple Single Page Application (SPA) focused on cybersecurity awareness.
The project aims to help users learn how to identify phishing emails through interactive examples
and feedback.

## Project Status
🚧 Early development – initial HTML, CSS, and JavaScript scaffolding in place.

## Technologies Used
- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (vanilla)

(Only technologies covered in the module are used.)

## Current Features
- Basic project structure
- HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files linked correctly
- Development environment set up using VS Code and Live Server

## Planned Features
- Display simulated emails
- Allow users to classify emails as phishing or legitimate
- Provide feedback explaining phishing indicators
- Simple scoring system

## Development Notes
This repository is version-controlled using Git and GitHub.
Commits are made incrementally to demonstrate the development process,
including mistakes, fixes, and refactoring where appropriate.

